# Important events

Conferences, demos, board meetings, customer reviews, product launches
— anything time-sensitive worth remembering. The orchestrator surfaces
upcoming events in `/status` and `/brief` to keep the company aware of
what's coming.

This file is **instance property** — owned by the company, never
overwritten by `/sync`. Add events by hand.

## Format

```
## <YYYY-MM-DD> · <title>
- **Type:** conference | demo | meeting | launch | review | other
- **When:** <YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM in local time, or date range>
- **Where:** <location or link>
- **Who:** <attendees / audience>
- **Goal:** <one-line — what success looks like>
- **Prep:** <anything we need to ready>
- **Notes:** <freeform>
```

When an event passes, move it down to **Past** — don't delete. Old
past events (>12 months) can be archived to `events-archive.md` or
trimmed.

## Upcoming

*Newest at the top, soonest at the bottom.*

_(populate)_

